<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,871,1864]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,328,987,1013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The new species is easily distinguished by the apically narrowing palpal bulb which has a protuberance on retrolateral surface (
<figureCitation box="[586,678,1026,1052]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="10.[151,271,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[249,1344,189,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1369,187,1765]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Opopaea sanya sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male carapace, dorsal view; D. Male scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view. Scale lines: A, B, D = 0.1 mm; C = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205799/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[641,656,1026,1052]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
B
</figureCitation>
), the posterior eye row which is procurved from above, the very large book lung covers, and the weakly developed scutal ridges (
<figureCitation box="[908,1003,1065,1091]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="10.[151,271,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[249,1344,189,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1369,187,1765]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Opopaea sanya sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male carapace, dorsal view; D. Male scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view. Scale lines: A, B, D = 0.1 mm; C = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205799/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[963,978,1065,1091]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
D
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,871,1864]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,1103,1129]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">Description:</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[437,543,1104,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
) (
<collectionCode box="[566,653,1104,1130]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crjh-4ne1" name="Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">IZCAS</collectionCode>
Ar 
<number box="[699,777,1104,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="19313.0">19313</number>
). Yellow species with yellowish legs. Body length 
<number box="[1376,1431,1104,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.21">1.21</number>
; carapace 
<number box="[263,316,1142,1168]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.58">0.58</number>
long, 
<number box="[394,446,1142,1168]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.42">0.42</number>
wide; abdomen 
<number box="[647,700,1142,1168]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.65">0.65</number>
long, 
<number box="[777,829,1142,1168]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.42">0.42</number>
wide. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1078,1213,1142,1168]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Figs 
<number box="[1138,1149,1142,1168]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
F, M
</figureCitation>
. Sides of carapace with finely longitudinal streaks; dorsal area smooth with some hairs at lateral edges. Eyes six, well developed, ALE and PME nearly equal sized, PLE smallest; posterior eye row procurved from above; ALE nearly touching, ALE-PLE separated by less than ALE radius, PME touching throughout most of their length, PLE- PME separated by less than PME radius (
<figureCitation box="[654,749,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="10.[151,271,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[249,1344,189,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1369,187,1765]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Opopaea sanya sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male carapace, dorsal view; D. Male scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view. Scale lines: A, B, D = 0.1 mm; C = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205799/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[711,726,1297,1323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
C
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus margin unmodified; clypeus height about 
<number box="[1384,1437,1297,1323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.25">1.25</number>
times of ALE diameter. Sternum longer than wide, uniform, fused to carapace; radial furrows present between coxae I-II, II-III, III-IV; surface smooth, without pits, microsculpture absent. Anterior end of endites with a small, sharply pointed projection. Legs short, thick and spineless. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[1239,1291,1413,1439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.21">1.21</number>
(
<number box="[1307,1363,1413,1439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[1376,1431,1413,1439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.24">0.24</number>
, 
<number box="[151,206,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.26">0.26</number>
, 
<number box="[219,274,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[286,342,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.13">0.13</number>
); II 
<number box="[392,444,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.02">1.02</number>
(
<number box="[461,517,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[530,585,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[598,653,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[665,720,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[733,790,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.13">0.13</number>
); III 
<number box="[849,901,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.84">0.84</number>
(
<number box="[918,974,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.26">0.26</number>
, 
<number box="[987,1042,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.13">0.13</number>
, 
<number box="[1055,1110,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.16">0.16</number>
, 
<number box="[1122,1177,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[1190,1245,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.11">0.11</number>
); IV 
<number box="[1307,1359,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.34">1.34</number>
(
<number box="[1375,1431,1452,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.39">0.39</number>
, 
<number box="[151,208,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[221,278,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.32">0.32</number>
, 
<number box="[291,348,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.26">0.26</number>
, 
<number box="[361,420,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="0.16">0.16</number>
). Leg formula: 
<number box="[611,628,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[647,658,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[677,694,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[713,728,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
. Abdominal dorsal scutum strongly sclerotized, punctate, covering full length of abdomen. Book lung covers large, ovoid, without setae. Pedicel tube short, ribbed, with narrow, dorsolateral, triangular extensions, scuto-pedicel region with weakly developed scutal ridges (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="10.[151,271,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[249,1344,189,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1369,187,1765]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Opopaea sanya sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male carapace, dorsal view; D. Male scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view. Scale lines: A, B, D = 0.1 mm; C = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205799/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,1606,1632]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
D
</figureCitation>
), scutum not extending far dorsal of pedicel. Sperm pore small, clearly discernible, transverse; posteriorly directed apodemes present. Colulus very small, with two short setae; spinneret scutum present, incomplete ring. Supra-anal scutum absent. Patella of palp greatly enlarged and swollen, attached to femur subbasally; cymbium completely fused to bulb without suture line; embolus complex, with small palpal depression (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="10.[151,271,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[249,1344,189,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1369,187,1765]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Opopaea sanya sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male carapace, dorsal view; D. Male scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view. Scale lines: A, B, D = 0.1 mm; C = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205799/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Figs 
<number box="[151,165,1761,1787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
A, B
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,871,1864]" box="[198,423,1800,1826]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
